
[1]homiletical

   HOMILET'ICAL, a. [ Gr. to converse in company.]

   1. Pertaining to familiar intercourse; social; conversable;
   companionable.

   2. Homiletic theology, a branch of practical theology, which teaches
   the manner in which ministers of the gospel should adapt their
   discourses to the capacities of their hearers, and pursue the best
   methods of instructing them by their doctrines and examples. It is also
   called pastoral theology.
